[[File:Planets Align Over La Silla.jpg|thumb|An [[syzygy (astronomy)|alignment]] of three planets over the summit of [[La Silla Observatory]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Planets Align Over La Silla |url=http://www.eso.org/public/images/potw1418a/ |work=ESO Picture of the Week |publisher=[[European Southern Observatory]] |accessdate=2014-05-10}}</ref>]]

A '''celestial event''' is an [[astronomy|astronomical]] [[phenomenon]] of interest that involves one or more [[astronomical object|celestial objects]]. Some examples of celestial events are the [[lunar phase|cyclical phase]]s of the [[Moon]], [[solar eclipse|solar]] and [[lunar eclipse]]s, [[transit (astronomy)|transits]] and [[occultation]]s, planetary [[opposition (planets)|oppositions]] and [[conjunction (astronomy)|conjunctions]], [[meteor shower]]s, and [[comet]] flybys.

