{{Unreferenced|date=February 2009}}
The '''Environmentally Sensitive Areas Scheme''' was an agri-environment scheme run by the [[United Kingdom|UK]] Government within the 22 designated [[Environmentally Sensitive Area]]s.

The scheme was superseded in 2005 by the [[Environmental Stewardship]] schemes.

