{{Italic title}}
'''''Progress in Photovoltaics''''' is a monthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering research on [[photovoltaics]]. It is published by [[John Wiley & Sons]] and the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Martin Green (professor)|Martin A. Green]] ([[University of New South Wales]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2013 [[impact factor]] of  9.696, ranking it 4th out of 83 journals in "Energy & Fuels",<ref name=WoS1>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Energy & Fuels |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> 9th out of 136 journals in "Physics Applied",<ref name=WoS2>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Physics Applied |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> and 15th out of 251 journals in "Materials Science Multidisciplinary".<ref name=WoS3>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Materials Science Multidisciplinary |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>

