{{refimprove|date=December 2015}}

[[File:RomaTempioNinfe1.jpg|thumb]]
The '''Temple of the Nymphs''' was a temple in [[ancient Rome]] dedicated to the [[Nymphs]], evidenced in several sources and generally identified with the remains on what is now via delle Botteghe Oscure. It was founded in the 3rd century BC or the early 2nd century BC. It was damaged by a fire in the mid 1st century BC and probably also affected by the citywide fire in 80 AD. This temple was on the Campus Martius.

==Bibliography==
